# Page sanity checks

After editing **landing cards**, **track hubs**, **relative paths** to `common/`, or **external `<a href="https://...">` links**, run:

```bash
node scripts/sanity-pages.js
```

This verifies:

- Root **`index.html`** still has **Hyperscale**, **Solana Core**, **Cryptography**, and **ZK** cards plus the glossary link.
- **`hyperscale/index.html`**, **`crypto-fintech/index.html`**, **`zk/index.html`**, **`solana-core/index.html`**, **`common/glossary.html`**, **`animations/index.html`**: local **CSS/JS** paths resolve to existing files.
- Every module listed in **`common/course-data.js`**, **`common/crypto-course-data.js`**, and **`common/zk-course-data.js`**: same asset checks; **`http(s)`** links use **`target="_blank"`** and **`rel`** including **`noopener`**.
- All **`solana-core/**/*.html`** pages: same checks.

Use alongside **`node verify-paths.js`** (path contract) and **`bash test-all.sh`** for broader checks.
